FBIS4-47910 "drafr087_c_94002" FBIS-AFR-94-087 Daily Report 4 May 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA 10 May Declared Public Holiday 10 May Declared Public Holiday MB0405165794 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in English 1600 GMT 4 May 94 MB0405165794 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network English BFN [Text] The cabinet has decided to declare 10 May, the date of the inauguration of the new president, a public holiday. The cabinet said in a statement it was well aware that the recent series of unscheduled public holidays had created serious disruptions and problems for organized commerce and industry. However, it had received strong recommendations in favor of the day being a public holiday from the Transitional Executive Council and the National Inauguration Committee.
